      "body" : "Seems like a no-brainer improvement if github really brought this stuff back. (people trusting a random third party's SSL for this is really concerningÃ¢ÂÂ they should be checking the signatures provided by the package, but I doubt it could make anything worse at this point).\r\n\r\n(Though I do wonder when we're going to have hosts become uncomfortable with the size of the bounty we're creating for hacking their servicesÃ¢ÂÂ¦)\r\n",
